The works and methodologies of A.Dundes and L.Honko will be studied from a comparative point of view, focusing both on their differences and common features. The following concepts, problems and topics will be discussed: psychoanalysis and the psychological approach, structuralism, the comparative method, variation, type, genre, fakelore, ethics.Objectives/eesmärkid:  to become acquainted with the scholarly legacy two classics in folkloristics  -  Alan Dundes and Lauri Honko - and their contribution to international folkloristics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1)	student knows the folkloristic works of Alan Dundes and Lauri Honko
2)	is able to analyze them critically
3)	can connect them with trends in international folkloristics
